<body>
    <h1>
        Honeywell Aerospace
        <br />
        LC&E Compliance Questionnaire Rev. 20
    </h1>
    <h2>Section 1:  Overview</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Identify the project/program, governing process(es) and team members involved in project planning.
                <ul>
                    <li>a. Program Name:  @ViewBag.partner.name</li>
                    <li>b. Designation (e.g., VE ####, G00###, etc.): @ViewBag.partner.address1</li>
                    <li>c. Program Leader/Manager: @ViewBag.Manager</li>
                    <li>
                        d. Governing process (e.g., Triage, Value Engineering, Standard Transition Process-STP, Other):
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62353 /> Standard Transition Process-STP
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62354 /> Triage
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62355 /> Value Engineering
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62356 /> Other
                    </li>
                    <li>e. Insert document link to project folder where due diligence and documentation is stored:</li>
                    <li>f. Identify the functional representatives involved in Project Planning (e.g., E&T, M&PM, ISC-VE, GS&I, SS):</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br/>
                2. Provide a general description of the project including the following:
                <ul>
                    <li>a. Project Description (provide overview of project): @Html.Raw(ViewBag.partner.dunsNumber)</li>
                    <li>
                        b. If the Project is Transition related, which type of activity is this?
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.ActivityType270 /> Make to Make Transition (HON to HON)
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.ActivityType269 /> Make to Buy (Outsourcing)
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.ActivityType267 /> Buy to Buy (Supplier to Supplier)
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> Build to Print (BTP)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> Build to Spec (ASL)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> Supplier Reposition
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.ActivityType268 />Buy to Make (In sourcing)
                        <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.ActivityType266 />Other
                    </li>
                    
                    
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br/>
                3. Is there an assist or non-recurring payment?
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35500_Yes /> Yes
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35500_No /> No
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                4. Does this product involve new designs or reuse?
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35501_Yes /> Yes
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35501_No /> No
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>Section 2: Transitions to China</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Does the transition/reposition contemplate movement of any parts to or within China for manufacture?
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35505_Yes /> Yes.
                <br /><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35505_No /> No. Skip the remainder of this Section 2 and proceed to Section 3.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. For each part contemplated for transition/reposition to or within China, please answer the following:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        a. In the CID file, was a usage code other than "C" (e.g., "CM", "MC", "M", "OT") found in the "Smart Usage Code" column of the "Workbook" tab?
                        <ul>
                            <li><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35506_Yes /> Yes.</li>
                            <li><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35506_No /> No. Skip the remainder of this Section 2 for this particular part.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        b. Is the part a programmable electronic component OR is it used on any of the following military platforms?
                        <ul>
                            <li style="margin-left:50px">
                            - US Government technology demonstrators
                            </li>
                            <li style="margin-left:50px">
                                - B-1B, B-2, B-21
                            </li>
                            <li style="margin-left:50px">
                                - F-15SE, F/A-18E/F, F-22, F-35, F-17
                            </li>
                            <li style="margin-left:50px">
                                - EA-18G
                            </li>
                            <li style="margin-left:50px">
                                - Abrams 1
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35509_Yes /> Yes. Part cannot be transitioned - remove from transition. Skip the remainder of this Section 2 for this particular part.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35509_No /> No. Proceed to the next question.
                            </li>
                            </ul>
</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                3. Is the drawing assigned a Military technology export classification (TEC) code, regardless of the country of current design authority (CDA) to be confirmed by
                the Approver/Export Compliance for this Section? A military technology export classification is any Department of State ITAR/USML item, as well as any Department
                of Commerce 500 or 600 series item.
                <ul>
                    <li><span style="font-style:italic;">Instructions</span>: Approver for this Section to mark "Y" in the "USML/500/600 (Y/N)" column of the "Project Scope" tab of the Scope and Export Data file.</li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35508_Yes /> Yes. Part <strong style="font-style:italic;">cannot</strong> be transitioned. Skip the remainder of this Section 2 for this particular part.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35508_No /> No. Question 4 of this Section 2 needs to be addressed.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
         <li>
             <br />
             4. Complete this question only AFTER LC&amp;E Checklist is approved.
             <br/>
             Fill in "China Optics" tab of the Project Scope file embedded in Section 1, Item 2c of this checklist. All US Government Platforms impacted by the contemplated transition must be identified. Send "China Optics" spreadsheet to Export Compliance for secondary review. After the checklist is approved by Export Compliance, send the completed spreadsheet to LC&E Checklist POC for General Counsel review and approval.
             <br/>
             <br/>
             General Counsel reviewed and approved on      .
         </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>Section 3: Export and Import</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Are the new suppliers listed on the Denied Parties List (Transition Manager must run check against the
                Denied Parties List in accordance with Aerospace Policy AP-1025)?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> N/A. The parts are being transitioned to a Honeywell site.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35512_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35512_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. Will any hardware manufacturing machines or equipment, tooling, fixtures and/or test equipment be
                provided to the receiving Honeywell site or new supplier?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35513_Yes />  Yes.
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        i.      If Yes, is the receiving Honeywell site or new supplier located offshore AND will the machine/tooling/test equipment be provided free of charge or at a reduced cost, AND will result in imports into the United States?
                        <br />
                        @if (ViewBag.Checkbox35513_Yes != string.Empty) {
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35514_Yes /><text> Yes.Provide the name of the person who is most familiar with the transition of the machine/ tooling / test equipment mentioned above.</text>
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35514_No /> <text>No.</text>
                                }
                        else
                        {
                            <input type="checkbox"/><text> Yes.Provide the name of the person who is most familiar with the transition of the machine/ tooling / test equipment mentioned above.</text>
                                <br />
                                <input type="checkbox"  /> <text>No.</text>
                        }
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35513_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                3. Will the receiving Honeywell site or new supplier return the manufactured hardware exclusively to Honeywell in the US?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35515_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35515_No /> No. They will transfer hardware to located in .
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                4. Has the receiving Honeywell site or new supplier obtained all necessary export authorizations to return the
                manufactured hardware to Honeywell in the U.S. or to the entities identified in Question #3?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62357 /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62359 /> Pending. The proposed receiving Honeywell site or supplier is working on obtaining the necessary local country
                export authorizations.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62358 /> No. Obtain confirmation from local export focal(s) that no export authorizations are required.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                5. For any parts transitioned/repositioned outside the US, which will be shipped back to a US site, has the
                HTSUS (Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States) submittal been completed to prevent customs delays?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35517_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35517_No /> No.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>Section 4:  IP Compliance</h2>
    <p>
        <h3>A.   Third Party Proprietary Information (Buy to Buy & Make to Buy & Buy to Make & OIP)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Can Honeywell and the new supplier (if applicable) execute this project using only documents and information that were/are created solely by Honeywell or the new supplier (if applicable) or are clearly within the public domain?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35521_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35521_No /> No/Not sure, contact IP Counsel for further reevaluation.
                <ul>
                    <li><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62362 /> i.  IP Counsel contacted on @ViewBag.Q1024, risk was cleared with recommendation to proceed.</li>
                    <li><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox62363 /> ii. IP Counsel contacted on @ViewBag.Q1024, risk acknowledged and characterized for consideration by transition business stakeholders.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>B.    Reverse Engineering (Buy to Buy & Buy to Make)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                2. As part of this project, will Honeywell need to "Reverse Engineer" the current supplier's part or provide the current supplier's part to the new supplier?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35524_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35524_No /> No. Skip remainder of Sub-Section B Reverse Engineering and proceed to Sub-Section C People and Stored Information.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                3. Has the Sourcing L&C representative (if unsure, verify with the cognizant commodity manager or use assignment list to identify the Sourcing L&C representative) reviewed the Contract, PIA and purchase orders of the current supplier to ensure there are no prohibitions related to Honeywell using the part for these purposes and provided guidance on information that may be shared during reverse-engineering process?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35525_Yes />  Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35525_No /> No. Please explain why not:_______
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>C.     People and Stored Information (Buy to Buy & Buy to Make)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>
                4. Does any Honeywell employee that will participate in the project (including members of the Engineering & Technology, Marketing & Product Management, and Integrated Supply Chain functions) have knowledge of the
                current supplier's proprietary information that will be relevant to the employee's role in the project
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35527_Yes /> Yes. Consult with the Souring L&C representative to provide the guidance on what proprietary information can be shared with the supplier.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35527_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                5. Does Honeywell have stored information (e.g., PDM, Team Center, etc.) that is proprietary to the current supplier and that is relevant to the part or product?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35528_Yes /> Yes. Consult with the Souring L&C representative to provide the guidance on what proprietary information can be shared with the supplier.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35528_No /> No.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>D.    Third Party Patents (Buy to Buy & Buy to Make)</h3>
        Is this a Build to Specification transition?
        <br />
        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35529_No /> No. Skip remainder of Sub-Section D and proceed to Sub-Section E.
        <br />
        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35529_Yes /> Yes. Proceed to next question.
        <ul>
            <li>
                6. Do you have documentation identifying when Honeywell first sold and/or delivered a product or assembly containing this part?
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35530_Yes /> Yes. Identify the date of delivery and/or sale and identity of supporting document(s):
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                First sale date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  First delivery date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supporting document(s):
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35530_No />  No. Do you have documentation, such as a schematic, which identifies the first production-approved version of the part?
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35534_No /> i. No.
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35534_Yes /> ii. Yes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Date of first production-approved design:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Supporting document(s):

                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>

            <li>
                <br />
                7.   Does the part or associated documentation include any patent markings? 
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35537_Yes /> Yes, consult with IP counsel and provide patent numbers or patent markings:
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35537_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                8.   Is patent infringement a significant risk for any part(s) to be transitioned?  High patent infringement risk parts include newer parts that include specific technology or features that are only currently available from the current supplier.  Low patent infringement risk parts include those parts that have been in production for a significant period of time (more than 20 years) years and include technology or features that are commonly available from other suppliers.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35538_Yes /> Yes, consult with IP counsel and provide details regarding the current supplier and part(s) to be transitioned.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35538_No /> No.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h3>E.    Third Party Licenses (Buy to Buy & Make to Buy & OIP)</h3>
      
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Does the transition scope include transfer of any software, tooling or test/manufacturing equipment?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35539_No /> No. Skip remainder of Sub-Section E and proceed to Section 5.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35539_Yes />  Yes. Proceed to next question.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. Are there any third party intellectual property licenses that will need to be transferred or assigned to the new supplier?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35542_Yes /> Yes, consult the Sourcing L&C representative to review the identified licenses to determine what can be transferred or assigned to the new supplier.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35542_No /> No. Skip remainder of Sub-Section E and proceed to Section 5.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>


    <h2>Section 5(a):  Channel 2 Customer Contracts</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Are there Distribution Channel 02, FAR Part 12, FAR Part 15, or Foreign Military Sales (FMS) orders in the Final CFDB file?
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" /> Yes - mark each field below as applicable:
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> Distribution Channel 02
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> "FAR Part 15 applies" = "Y"
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> "FAR Part 12 applies" = "Y"
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" /> "FMS" = "Y"
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" /> No - Skip the remainder of this Section 5(a) and proceed to Section 5(b) of the checklist.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. Site Capability/Supplier Responsibility Verification - Answer (a), or (b), as applicable to the transition type.
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        a. <strong>Make to Make and Buy to Make Transitions</strong> - Has the proposed receiving site been confirmed as capable of performing U.S. Government and use contracts?
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                FAR Part 15 work (e.g. CAS, TINA)
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Site capability confirmed.</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> N/A - no FAR 15 work</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                FAR Part 12 work
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Site capability confirmed.</li>
                                    <li ><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> N/A - no FAR 12 work</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Berry Amendment and Other Domestic Preference Restrictions
                                <ul>
                                    <li ><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Site capability confirmed.</li>
                                    <li ><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                DPAS
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Site capability confirmed.</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                SectK Reps &amp; Certs (FAR 52.203-15, DFARS 252.206-7000, DFARS 252.225-7028)
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Site capability confirmed.</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        b. <strong>OIP, Make to Buy, Buy to Buy, and Supplier Reposition Transitions</strong> - Has supplier responsibility been validated via AP-1802 by Sourcing Compliance (<strong>Kevin R. Walker</strong>) for performance of U.S. Government end use contracts?
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                FAR Part 15 work (e.g. CAS, TINA)
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Supplier responsibility validated</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> N/A - no FAR 15 work</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                FAR Part 12 work
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Supplier responsibility validated</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> N/A - no FAR 12 work</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                DPAS
                                <ul>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Supplier responsibility validated</li>
                                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                SectK Reps &amp; Certs (FAR 52.203-15, DFARS 252.206-7000, DFARS 252.225-7028)
                                <ul>
                                    <li ><input type="checkbox" /> Yes. Supplier responsibility validated</li>
                                    <li ><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                                </ul>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                3. Have you confirmed all applicable FAR Part 15, FAR Part 12, DPAS and SectK Reps &amp; requirements have been flowed down and accepted in the supplier contract?
                <ul>
                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> Yes (evidenced in supplier self-assessment letter)</li>
                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> No. why?</li>
                    <li><input type="checkbox" /> N/A (Make to Make or Buy to Make)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                4. Using the Final CFDB, complete the actions in the table below as applicable to your project type:
            </li>
        <li>
            <br />
            5. Classified Contracts - <strong>Make to Make, OIP, and Make to Buy Transitions</strong> - Has the proposed receiving site been identified by Aero Chief Security Officer (<strong>Jeff Miller</strong>) as requiring further analysis?
            <ul>
                <li><input type="checkbox" /> No - Proceed to Section 5(b) of the checklist</li>
                <li><input type="checkbox"/> Yes - Contact USG End Use Contracts POC (<strong>Jana Moodie</strong>) for determination on mitigating actions</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
     
        <li>
            6.  For Make to Maake, OIP, and Make to Buy transitions, copy USG End Use contracts POC (<strong>Jana Moodie</strong>) on handoff of outstanding actions between Phase 2 and Phase 3, and provide SharePoint access/link to where documentations of action completion is stored.
        </li>
        </ul>
    </p>


    <h2>Section 5(b): Channel 1 Customer Contracts</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Within the CFDB for the parts to be transitioned/repositioned, was a Channel 1 contract found?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35563_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35563_No /> No. Skip the remainder of this Section 5(b) and proceed to Section 6.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. FAA Notification: For all "01" Distribution parts contained within CFDB Final, transitioning or repositioning to a
