                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" />   No.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <br />
                        b.       Have Customer approvals and/or notifications been requested and completed for all customers with approval and/or notification requirements applicable to the transition/reposition?
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" />  No, requirements have been added to the TAC 3 RAIL.
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" />  N/A, no customers require notification or approval.
                    </li>

                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <h2>Section 6: Buy American Act</h2>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Within the CID for the parts to be transitioned/repositioned, were any usage codes other than "C" found (e.g., "CM", "MC", "M", "OT")?
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35570_Yes />  Yes.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35570_No /> No. If No, does the CFDB show any Channel 02 orders?
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35571_Yes />  Yes. Proceed to Question 2 in this section.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35571_No /> No. Provide email from the Approver for this Section stating a "Not Required" for this Section. Skip the remainder of this Section 6 and proceed to Section 7.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. Is the project a US to US transition/reposition where the substantial transformation of the part is occurring within the US with greater than 50% Domestic content?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35573_Yes /> Yes. Attach evidence confirming US Content and build, then skip the remainder of this Section 6 and proceed to Section 7.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35573_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                3. Have the parts in this project gone through a BAA review under a different project name/number or CID request?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35574_Yes /> Yes. Please identify Project#, CID and BAA returned date:
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35574_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                4. Has the project scope changed from previous BAA reviews through a change in "Country Transitioning To" or a change in part scope (additions) since the BAA Response was returned to you?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35575_Yes /> Yes. Please resubmit BAA analysis for review.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35575_No /> No.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                5. Was the BAA review for this project performed more than 6 months prior to your submission of this LC&E checklist?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35572_Yes /> Yes. Please re-submit BAA analysis for review with new Final CFDB.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35572_No />  No.
                <br />
                The BAA Approver will provide a BAA Response File. Within your returned BAA Response File, the "BAA Response" tab contains all of the BAA associated legal and business risks, along with actions to mitigate.
                <br />
                Three columns "Award Country", "Documentation Type and Approver" and "Action Status" must be filled out for question 6 below <a>along with your embedded file or link.</a> For all Business or Legal risks identified, there must be an approved closure response or change in scope identified within the "Documentation Type" and "Approver" cells.
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                6. Have you completed all of the required BAA actions for the award country or modified scope as defined in your BAA Response File?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35576_Yes /> Yes. Please embed files, emails or link to diligence sharesite below.
               
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35576_No />   No, part scope/countries have been redefined to mitigate risks and are updated within the "Response" tab of the attached BAA_Reponse File (See column labeled "Award Country (to be completed by
                requestor)").
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <h2>Section 7: Berry Amendment and Other Domestic Preference Restrictions</h2>
    <p>
        <input type="checkbox" /> N/A. Check here if (i) no Channel 2 Customer Contracts were found in the Final CFDB, and (ii) all CID usage codes are "C".
        If N/A, then skip the remainder of this Section 7 and proceed to Section 8.

        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Berry Amendment: Has Sourcing Compliance (Kevin R. Walker) confirmed Supplier's ability to comply with Berry Amendment?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> Yes (evidenced in verification of supplier responsibility documentation)
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> No, why?
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" /> N/A (Make to Make, Buy to Make, or Supplier Reposition project where Supplier does not change)
            </li>
            <li>
                <br />
                2. Other Domestic reference Restrictions:
               <ul>
                   <li>a. Does the project include products that qualify as: (1) roller or ball bearings or components thereof; of (2) hand or measuring tools?
                   
                       <br/><input type="checkbox" /> Yes
                       <br /><input type="checkbox" /> No - Skip to Section 8
                   </li>
                   <li>
                       <br />
                       b. Will the transition cause the product to be manufactured or produced outside of the United States:
                       <br /><input type="checkbox" /> Yes - do not proceed without ISC  General Counsel approval
                       <br /><input type="checkbox" /> No
                   </li>
               </ul>
            </li>
            
        </ul>
    </p>
    <h2>Section 8: Supplier Contracts (Supplier Relationship)</h2>
    <p>
        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.CheckboxS8_Na/> N/A. Check here if this is not a Buy to Buy or Buy to Make transition. If N/A, then skip the remainder of this Section 8 and proceed to Section 9.
        <br />
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Please identify the ISC commodity manager for each part/product impacted by the project as well as the contract number (and
                type) or PO number under which this item is currently procured:

                <br />
                <br />
                <br />
                Commodity Manager&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Contract Number (and Type) or PO Number
                <br />
                <br />
                <br />
                <br />
                <br />
                <br />
            </li>
            <li>
                2. With assistance from the identified commodity manager, determine whether the current procurement contract prohibits or
                limits Honeywell's right to move the source of the product to another source at Honeywell's discretion.
                <br />

                @if (ViewBag.CheckboxS8_Na== "checked")
                {
                    <text>
                    <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.Describe prohibitions or limitations: 
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox"  />  No.
                </text>
                }
                else
                {
                    <text>
                    <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35590_Yes /> Yes.Describe prohibitions or limitations: @ViewBag.Checkbox35590_Comment
                        <br />
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35590_No />  No.
                </text>
                }
            <li>
                <br />
                3. Has Honeywell ever entered into an agreement wherein Honeywell sold the business related to this part or agreed not to
                compete in the manufacture or sale of the part?
                <br />

@if (ViewBag.CheckboxS8_Na == "checked")
{
    <text>

                <input type="checkbox" /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" />  No.
                </text>
}
else
{
    <text>

                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35591_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35591_No />  No.
    </text>
}

</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <h2>Section 9: Offset</h2>
    <p>
        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.CheckboxS9_Na /> N/A. Check here if this is a Make to Make, Make to buy, Buy to make, or OIP transition. If N/A, then skip the remainder of this Section 9.
        <br />
        <ul>
            <li>
                1. Do any of the transition/reposition parts currently support offset requirements for the jurisdiction in which they are currently
                manufactured or from which they are currently sourced? Discuss with Offset Council to answer following questions.
                <br />
                <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox35595_Yes /> Yes.
                <br />
